        <h3><strong>Giving back to the Community</strong></h3>
        <h5><small>by Serena Applebee on 13 February 2014</small></h5>
         <p>  I grew up poor with a single mom as my family's only provider. Life was difficult, but Mom had made everything seem better. She was resourceful and independent - an entrepeneur in every sense. So when she started her own business, I was certain that she would succeed. Of course that wasn't case. The business barely stayed afloat for the first few years. She was going to declare bankruptcy until a member of Women Entrepeneurs Society invested in the business. We had more money to improve our products and pump up advertising. After a few months, we started generating a profit and after 3 years, we we'd managed to expand the business to a few other branches. I will forever be thankful to that woman. </p>

        <p>  Through Rebound.Me, I was able to connect with women who were in the same situation I had been. Being an entrepeneur is tough, more so when you're struggling to raise kids at the same time. I'm very blessed to have achieved the success of my business - and I want to empower other women so that they may find the same path. </p>

