        <h3><strong>Journey of Re-Discovery</strong></h3>
        <h5><small>by Serena Applebee on 13 February 2014</small></h5>
        <p>  After my first divorce, I spent the following months in a zombie-like daze. I went out more often in the first two weeks than I had in the previous year, I drank more than my body would have appreciated, and I began to take a pessimistic approach to life. After a couple of months in this routine (if you could call it that), I began to realise I was losing sight of myself – who I was, who I wanted to be, and what I should be doing to get out of that point. I came across Rebound.Me and out of decided to purchase a trip to Paris. . </p>

            <p>  The following months were consumed by packing and preparing for the trip and I soon forgot – or more accurately neglected – how lost and confused I was feeling after the divorce. Rebound.Me had made my stay in Paris both an enjoyable and eye-opening experience – had I not found their website on that unforsaken Sunday evening, I would probably still be watching “Sex in the City” with a bottle on whisky on my bed. I was lost and hurt – I needed to rediscover myself and through traveling I realised how easy, simple, and completely normal it was to stand on my own two feet. I moved on. </p>
  
